sub_title: English and Academic Skills Teacher at Study Group
summary:
My classes are based on 3 principles. First, creating a safe and fun, ‘I want to be in’, class environment for students and teachers is central. Second, making mistakes, but continue trying is encouraged and an explicit part of the learning process—everybody can learn. Third, respect and tolerance for and from all members of the classroom are fundamental.
With over 15 years of teaching English and theatre to students of different ages and needs, I have dedicated my professional life to finding effective ways of teaching and learning. Understanding that education is a complex process, I have adopted a flexible, eclectic teaching approach which allows me not only to adapt to my students’ learning necessities but also grants me a virtually endless supply of teaching activities.
My interest in education has also brought me to work in other areas such as founding and directing two performing arts clubs for students, research, and preparing and conducting workshops for colleagues. Right now, I am finishing my second master’s degree in Literature and Education in English at Universiteit Van Amsterdam, providing me with more useful tools to help students achieve their goals.
